-- China Buys 2.5 Million Tons of Cotton for Reserve, Cncotton Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-02-08T10:21:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/china-buys-2-5-million-tons-of-cotton-for-reserve-cncotton-says.html
China, the world’s biggest cotton
consumer, bought more than 2.5 million metric tons of the fiber
from the domestic market since September to replenish state
reserves, according to industry website cncotton.com.  Purchases have totaled 2,503,860 tons, representing about
38 percent of the country’s total cotton output last year,
according to Bloomberg News calculations based on data from
cncotton.com and the National Bureau of Statistics. Output
gained 10.7 percent in 2011 to 6.6 million tons, according to
the statistics bureau.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Feiwen Rong in Beijing at 
